Another Example

You must learn to embrace the
API

Math Class

Remember from before
• The caret (^) does NOT indicate
exponentiation
• In other words, in Java, 2^3 does not
equal 8
• There is another way to do
exponentiation; maybe it is in the Math
class?

Math Example
public class MorePower
{
public static void main(String[] args)
{
double base = 2.0;
double exponent = 3.0;
System.out.println(Math.pow(base,exponent));
}//end method main
}//end class MorePower

.

Math Example

When to Use the Variable/Class
Name
• Does the "Modifier and Type" column of
the method say "static"?
- Yes: Use Class name (typically uppercase
first letter)
- No: Use variable name (typically lowercase
first letter)
